## {#diff-rules data-menu-title="Rules for Differentiation"}

[Rules for Differentiation]{.slide-title}

<hr>

:::{.center-text}
**Constant Rule**
:::

- If $f(x)$ is contant, then for all $x$, $f'(x)=0$

$$
\begin{align}
&y=a &\frac{dy}{dx}=0
\end{align}
$$
<br>

:::{.center-text}

**Power Rule**
:::

$$
\frac{d}{dx}[x^n]
=nx^{n-1}
$$

